<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-11-28T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-11-28T08:00:00-05:00" n="147" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d147">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.00/2740</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-28T21:00:00+08:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 28, 1917, 9 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Resignation of General Tuan accepted. Minister of Foreign Affairs
                            designated temporal Premier. Have private information to the effect that
                            General Tuan would like to devote himself to work for assistance to
                            Allies in the war. I believe he could advantageously be intrusted with
                            this matter. His personal honesty and loyalty are generally recognized
                            and his appointment as high commissioner for the above purpose would be
                            widely approved.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>